      {q:"A 60-foot-long vehicle at 35 mph needs how many seconds of following distance?",options:["5 seconds","6 seconds","7 seconds","8 seconds"],answer:1,explanation:"60 ÷ 10 = 6 seconds; under 40 mph so no extra second.",handbook:"Keep 1 second of following distance for every 10 feet of length, plus 1 more over 40 mph.",hbref:"§2.6"}
